<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-11-29T23:59:59+03:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="148" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d148">
                            <head>No. 148<lb/><hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi></head>
                            <p>Secretary <persName corresp="#p_AD1">Acheson</persName> visited Bonn
                                May 23–26 for discussions with Foreign Secretary <persName corresp="#p_EASA1">Eden</persName>, Foreign Minister <persName corresp="#p_SR1">Schuman</persName>, and Chancellor <persName corresp="#p_AK1">Adenauer</persName> concerning contractual
                                relations and the European Defense Community. For the records of
                                their discussions, see <ref target="#d42">Documents 42</ref> ff.</p>
                        </div>
